<subSubSection id="01964FF464D93FF87F505DF9EB2AEA54" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="28C56C0E437A93366A85BDE4E2BFA623" pageId="50" pageNumber="81">Type locality. Caspian Sea (no details).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C92F70410037C9218709721216079D4" pageId="50" pageNumber="81">
Distribution. Middle and southern Caspian Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="FB71324CB36829C0F3713570A2BF22F8" pageId="50" pageNumber="81">Logvinenko and Starobogatov 1969</bibRefCitation>
). This species was mentioned from depths between 200 and 400 m in the South Caspian Basin of Azerbaijan (
<bibRefCitation id="574133B99B43361842FAE407F7063014" author="Mirzoev, GS" journalOrPublisher="International Journal of Zoological Studies" pageId="79" pageNumber="110" pagination="43 - 48" title="Zoobenthos distribution patterns in the deepwater horizon of Azerbaijan sector of the Caspian Sea." url="http://www.zoologyjournals.com/download/74/1-7-29-696.pdf" volume="2" year="2017">Mirzoev and Alekperov 2017</bibRefCitation>
, who reported the species as 
<taxonomicName id="76B605A5D1DF4A23447E3BFD684B7DF8" genus="T." lsidName="T. laticarinata" pageId="50" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="laticarinata">T. laticarinata</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CE62F094E4038A9B350C87905E34F013" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D05AAD491C86B8973D096D0D1E0E5B21" lastPageId="51" lastPageNumber="82" pageId="50" pageNumber="81">
Taxonomic notes. The species is characterised by a massive keel near the lower suture.? 
<taxonomicName id="8FC2898F5ED92A46E39B1F4066D58490" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Turricaspia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Turricaspia dimidiata" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="50" pageNumber="81" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="dimidiata">Turricaspia dimidiata</taxonomicName>
is distinguished based on its more centrally placed keel. This distinction is tentative and only based on comparison of available illustrations; we are aware of the possibility that these differences might not be diagnostic. Moreover, the keel seems to become stronger with increasing water depth (
<bibRefCitation id="257BFE642C9681E3284CF7CBCE4EB00C" author="Starobogatov, YaI" journalOrPublisher="Zoologicheskiy Zhurnal" pageId="83" pageNumber="114" pagination="875 - 886" title="Prakticheskiye priyomy sistematiki i vopros o kriterii vida." volume="47" year="1968">Starobogatov 1968</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="12B8D495AEAF89F904754E6A4FA83708" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Pyrgula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pyrgula laticarinata" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="51" pageNumber="82" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="laticarinata">
<pageBreakToken id="5740ACCEB202F5D55B99727523422694" pageId="51" pageNumber="82" start="start">Pyrgula</pageBreakToken>
laticarinata
</taxonomicName>
Logvinenko &amp; Starobogatov, 1969, which differs from 
<taxonomicName id="D4C8BEA71BA95D022F8C502B901AD935" genus="T." lsidName="T. basalis" pageId="51" pageNumber="82" rank="species" species="basalis">T. basalis</taxonomicName>
only in the strength of the keels, was considered a junior synonym by 
<bibRefCitation id="CBA84BDD8ED5F2525283B503A7651425" author="Neubauer, TA" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="80" pageNumber="111" pagination="43 - 103" title="A late Pleistocene gastropod fauna from the northern Caspian Sea with implications for Pontocaspian gastropod taxonomy." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.770.25365" volume="770" year="2018">Neubauer et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
